    • Method Detail

      • kind

        public SqlKind kind()
        Returns the kind of statement.

        Possibilities include:

        • Queries: usually SqlKind.SELECT, but other query operators such as SqlKind.UNION and SqlKind.ORDER_BY are possible
        • DML statements: SqlKind.INSERT, SqlKind.UPDATE etc.
        • Session control statements: SqlKind.COMMIT
        • DDL statements: SqlKind.CREATE_TABLE, SqlKind.DROP_INDEX
        Returns:
        Kind of statement, never null
